\documentclass[tikz,border=10pt]{standalone}
\usetikzlibrary{arrows.meta, positioning}

\begin{document}

\begin{tikzpicture}[>={Stealth[scale=0.8]}, node distance=1.5cm, every node/.style={align=center}]
    \node (agent) [circle, draw, inner sep=0.3em] {};

    \node [above left=1cm and 2cm of agent] (left-text) {State = (x,y)\\Reward = cx};

    \node [right=4cm of left-text] (right-text) {};
    \node [above=1cm of right-text] (+10) {+10};
    \node [below=1cm of right-text] (+1) {\scriptsize +1};
    \node [below=0.5cm of +10, dashed, rectangle, draw, inner sep=0.3em] (treadmill) {};
    \node [below=1cm of treadmill] (agent2) [circle, draw, inner sep=0.3em] {};
    \draw [-{Latex[scale=0.8]}] (treadmill.south) -- (agent2.north);
    \draw [-{Latex[scale=0.8]}] (agent2.north) -- (treadmill.south);

    \draw [-{Latex[scale=0.8]}] (left-text.east) -- (agent.west);
    \draw [-{Latex[scale=0.8]}] (agent2.east) -- (right-text.west);
\end{tikzpicture}

\end{document}
```

### Explanation:
- **Standalone Document Class**: Used to create a standalone document.
- **TikZ Library**: `arrows.meta` for modern arrow tips and `positioning` for easy node positioning.
- **Nodes**: 
  - `agent` and `agent2` represent the agent.
  - `left-text` and `right-text` are text boxes for descriptions.
  - `+10` and `+1` are numerical labels.
  - `treadmill` is a dashed rectangle to represent the treadmill.
- **Arrows**: Used to show interactions and movements between nodes.
- **Node Distances**: Adjusted to align the elements as in the image.

